# Privacy Policy for Qeleme Exams

**Effective Date: [2024/10/11]**

At **Qeleme Exams**, we are committed to safeguarding your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our mobile application (the “App”). By accessing or using the App, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this policy.

## 1. Information We Collect

### Personal Data
While using our App, we may ask you to provide certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you. This may include, but is not limited to:
- Name
- Institution Type (College or University)
- Name of Your College or University
- Phone Number
- Payment screenshot

### Usage Data
We may collect information on how the App is accessed and used (“Usage Data”). This may include details such as:
- Your device’s Internet Protocol (IP) address
- Time and date of your visit
- Unique device identifiers and other diagnostic data

## 2. Purpose of Data Use
We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
- To provide and maintain our App
- To notify you about updates or changes to the App
- To provide customer support and assistance
- To monitor the usage of the App
- To detect, prevent, and address technical issues
- To analyze usage patterns for service improvement

## 3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information in the following circumstances:
- To comply with legal obligations
- To protect and defend our rights and property
- To prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the App

## 4. Data Security
We are committed to ensuring the security of your personal information. We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

## 5. Third-Party Services
Our App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We do not control and are not responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party services. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services you engage with.

## 6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page, and we will update the “Effective Date” at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

